# Commit & branch discipline (binding)

Enforced locally by `scripts/hooks/` (pre-commit, commit-msg, pre-push) and authoritatively
by server-side branch protection on `main`.

- **One atomic, green commit per logical sub-step.** Never bundle unrelated work.
- **Every commit is green** — the test suite passes before committing. Never use `--no-verify`
  to dodge a red tree.
- **Conventional, milestone-scoped messages:** `feat(mN): …`, `test(mN): …`, `docs(mN): …`
  (also `fix|chore|refactor|perf|build|ci`).
- **One branch per milestone** (`feat/mN-…`). Never commit on `main`.
- **NEVER push. NEVER merge to `main`.** Pushes and merges are a human action at the
  milestone review gate. End each session with everything committed on the milestone
  branch and nothing pushed.
